-- VA Tech Wabag Wins $9 Million Water Treatment Contract in Turkey
-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 2013-01-24T11:48:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-24/va-tech-wabag-wins-9-million-water-treatment-contract-in-turkey.html
VA Tech Wabag Brno won a contract of
more than 7 million euros ($9.3 million) to build a water
treatment plant in  Turkey .  Vitkovice Power Engineering, the contractor for the plant,
placed the order, according to a  statement  on the Wabag group’s
website. The plant will treat water for the 290-megawatt Yunus
Emre power plant, under construction in Turkey’s Eskisehir
province.  The facility will clean 900 cubic meters of water per hour,
of which 850 cubic meters will be used to cool the power plant
and 40 cubic meters will be used by the plant boilers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rakteem Katakey in New Delhi at 
